commit.message: KEYS: New file describing how releases are signed and how to check them.
examples/hotplug_advanced.py: Fix syntax for python 3

travis.yml: Modernise.

sudo is deprecated and causing a warning.
dist is super outdated now, and its gcc failing to build current libusb1.
os is missing and causing a warning.
Release 1.8 .

Correct scaling of max power for Super Speed

The 'MaxPower' field of the Configuration descriptor is in units of 2mA
for everything pre-dating Super Speed and in units of 8mA for Super
Speed. Also, it is actually a current (measured in Amps), not a power
(measured in Watts); so the previous docstring was wrong/misleading when
it talked about mW (milliwatts).
libusb1: Fix libusb_control_transfer_get_data .

libusb1: Fix get_extra on python 2.7 .

Whereas single-item retrieval on a "bytes" instance yields a string and
hence requires an "ord" call, on "bytearray" instance it yields an integer
directly. This was broken by:
  commit b26f6cdbdb269ccf4d57965387071b21545cb912
  Author: Vincent Pelletier <plr.vincent@gmail.com>
  Date:   Sun Oct 16 11:14:04 2016 +0000

      Use writeable buffer for transfers (sync & async).
along with buffer_at cast to bytearray.

travis: Test against 3.5 and 3.6 .

Now that they are available in travis. 3.7 requires playing with package
repositories, so ignore it for now.

setup.py: Remove 2.4, 2.5 and 2.6 classifiers.

These have not been tested in years, they are likely broken.

libusb1: Use b-strings.

Removes one reason to have a version check here. This is supported since
2.6 .

setup.py: Fix "test" command with python3.

https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/issues/613

Fix getting of extra descriptors

Also add a test to check that getting of extra descriptors works
(requires a USB device with extra descriptors, such as a UVC webcam,
which has at least one InterfaceAssociation descriptor).

Bump to 1.7.1 .

Really just a README update, thanks to versioneer !
Fix versioneer: add forgotten setup.cfg file.
tests: Add trivial version presence test.
usb1: Use versioneer.

usb1: Keep __ctypesCallbackWrapper alive longer.

When calling "close" inside the callback (which at least happens if current
transfer has been "doom"ed before user callback returns), this instance
attribute was cleared, causing it to be possibly gabrage-collected before
code could return to libusb, causing occasional segfaults.
Fix typos in example code
Bump to 1.7 .
setup: Simplify.
Bump copyright year.

usb1: Expose transferred byte count and received bytes on synchronous API

So that it is usable when a USBErrorTimeout happens, making the timeout
parameter more useful.
Document access to these raised USBErrorTimeout instance properties.
usb1: Fix docstring interruptRead refering to itself.
Specify that it is compatible with python 3 in setup.py
README: libusb.org seems dead, switch to the fork.

usb1: Move getManufacturer, getProduct ,getSerialNumber to USBDeviceHandle.

Keep shortcuts for these on USBDevice.
Update USBDevice docstrings a bit to reflect that this class is intended
to mostly access OS-cached descriptor data (in addition to providing a
way to actually open a device).

usb1: get{,ASCII}StringDescriptor now return None for descriptor 0.

This descriptor contains the language list. It is binary data and not
an encoded string, so it would have very likely raised UnicodeDecodeError
anyway. It must be accessed using getSupportedLanguageList, which returns
a python-usable data structure.
Bump to 1.6.6 .

usb1: Expose string descriptors on USBDevice.

Depending on the OS and driver, it may be impossible to open the same
device multiple times, forbidding retrieval of manufacturer name,
product name and serial number once opened.
This allows calling getASCIIStringDescriptor on the already available
USBHandle instead.
Bump to 1.6.5 .
